Blue-Green Algae Update – Reservoir Park:

Samples from Reservoir Park that were tested at Dalhousie University found no detections of blue-green algae. 

With these results, the caution signs have been removed from the pond.

Suspected presence of cyanobacteria (blue-green algae) in the large pond of Reservoir Park. Additional testing is underway to confirm visual signs from initial sampling. The park remains open but people & pets should not to enter the larger pond until more test results are in.
